answers.body_markdown:
You can override [`object.__setattr__`](https://docs.python.org/3/reference/datamodel.html#object.__setattr__):

    class a_class:
        defined_var = 1
    
        def a_function(self):
            self.defined_var = 2
            self.undefined_var = 3
    
        def __setattr__(self, key, value):
            if hasattr(self, key):
                object.__setattr__(self, key, value)
            else:
                raise AttributeError(f&quot;\&quot;{key}\&quot; is not defined in \&quot;{self.__class__.__name__}\&quot;&quot;)
    
    a = a_class()
    print(a.defined_var)
    a.a_function()  # &lt;-- throws an error

**P.S.** `defined_var` is class variable shared by all instances. It means that all changes will affect all instances of class (maybe it&#39;s not what you&#39;re expecting). More information [here](https://docs.python.org/3/tutorial/classes.html#class-and-instance-variables).

